The President hosted a dinner with leaders from eleven Central and Eastern European countries in Prague. The leaders congratulated the President on the signing of the New START agreement between the US and Russia. They discussed the improvement in relations between Washington and Moscow, which has created new opportunities for them to improve their relations with Russia. They emphasized the importance of the Atlantic Alliance and global security. The President highlighted the relevance of Article 5 in addressing 21st century threats. They also reaffirmed their support for the NATO mission in Afghanistan and discussed the need to address Iran's failure to meet international obligations and promote stability in the Balkans. The leaders in attendance were from Bulgaria, Croatia, the Czech Republic, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, Romania, Slovakia, and Slovenia.